<title>CROATIA: Croatia March retail prices up 0.1 pct, 3.9 yr/yr.</title>
<headline>Croatia March retail prices up 0.1 pct, 3.9 yr/yr.</headline>
<dateline>ZAGREB 1997-04-03</dateline>
<text>
<p>The State Bureau of Statistics issued the following economic indicator details.</p>
<p> CROATIA RETAIL PRICES	   MARCH     FEBRUARY    MARCH '96</p>
<p> Monthly change (pct)	    +0.1	   0.0	  -0.1</p>
<p> Year-on-year			+3.9	  +3.7	  +3.3</p>
<p>NOTES -- January-March inflation was put at 1.0 percent compared to end of 1996, with the year-on-rise rise of 4.0 percent. Croatia introduced a radical anti-inflation programme in October 1993, when monthly inflation hit 38.7 percent. -- Zagreb Newsroom, 385-1-4557075</p>
